<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Generic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
The generic characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its differentiation from related genera are detailed in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" author="Wilkinson, C" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="407 - 517" refId="B26" refString="Wilkinson, C, 1968. A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London 31 (4): 407 - 517, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" title="A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" volume="31" year="1968">Wilkinson (1968)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jiang, S" journalOrPublisher="Entomotaxonomia" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="81 - 88" refId="B12" refString="Jiang, S, Han, HX, 2019. A new species of Ditrigona Moore (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae) in China, with a checklist to the triangularia -group. Entomotaxonomia 41 (2): 81 - 88" title="A new species of Ditrigona Moore (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae) in China, with a checklist to the triangularia - group." volume="41" year="2019">Jiang and Han (2019)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
The species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are mainly distributed in the Oriental region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="derocina species group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" author="Wilkinson, C" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="407 - 517" refId="B26" refString="Wilkinson, C, 1968. A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London 31 (4): 407 - 517, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" title="A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" volume="31" year="1968">Wilkinson (1968)</bibRefCitation>
placed three species in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bryk), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona diana" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona diana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wilkinson, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona pruinosa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pruinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona pruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Moore). The two former species have been recorded in China, and a further species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guo &amp; Cheng &amp; Jiang &amp; Xue &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Guo &amp; Cheng &amp; Jiang &amp; Xue &amp; Han" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Deroca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deroca crystalla" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crystalla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Deroca crystalla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chu &amp; Wang, 1987 is newly placed in this species group in this work.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
Species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group are characterized by unipectinate antennae and semi-transparent wings. In the male genitalia, the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is unusual in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having sclerotization of the vinculum, and a quite long and narrow aedeagus. The eighth sternite is distinguished by large and curved octavals, and the tergite protrudes strongly. The female genitalia are characterized by having a very long ductus bursae, an ostial plate, an accessory sac and a long and narrow signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
